HEADWORD: Hain
<hw>Hain</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Sw.
<ets>h⟦aum⟧gn</ets> hedge, inclosure, Dan. <ets>hegn</ets> hedge, fence.
See <er>Hedge</er>.]</ety> <def>To inclose for mowing; to set aside for
grass.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A ground . . . <xex>hained</xex> in.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

